Im not sure if I buy Into the idea of creating a system or a method that‚Äôs my own. I feel A LOT when I move because it‚Äôs a culmination & conversation of so many modalities and I don‚Äôt think there‚Äôs really one ‚Äòcomplete‚Äô or perfect system and I‚Äôm not about to reinvent the wheel when I‚Äôm barely touching the tip of the iceberg when it comes to knowledge. The classic notion of the more you learn, the more you realise you don‚Äôt know so much. It‚Äôs humbling. 
In one practice I feel my experience in all of these below:
Soft acrobatics 
Yoga 
Handbalancing 
Tricking 
Capoeira (which underpins most of it and the thing I‚Äôve done the least sadly but that‚Äôs changing!) 
Calisthenics 
Weightlifting 
Meditation 
Breathwork 
Martial arts like BJJ 
& lots of PLAY, failure, trial & error, dancing around and figuring it out. 
This is my take on all of this and, without going down the rabbit hole of social conditioning and late stage capitalism / what drives us to want to monetise EVERYTHING ever, I just don‚Äôt want to trademark anything. 
Not at this stage in my life anyway. 
Feel free to share your feels on this - especially the other teachers out there!
